HEALTH Division
Improving health and wellbeing around the globe
Research Analyst – qualitative studies (H/F)
With social sciences, sociology, and /or healthcare knowledge.
CDI.
Kantar Health Division has an open position for a Research Analyst for qualitative studies with a strong interest in medical researches and healthcare as a whole. Reporting to a Project Manager / Project Director / Project Lead, you will work primarily on international qualitative healthcare projects within the EPI/HEOR (Epidemiology/ Health Economics and Outcome Research) team. Committed to client service and research excellence, you will be expected to support the project team to deliver on client requests. To be successful, you, in conjunction with the project team, will be fully involved in all the stages of research studies, from the study set up to the final delivery/report and will be a key player in the analysis of the studies.
Kantar, Health Division helps life sciences companies develop products that improve people’s lives and well-being. Their blend of consulting, data analytics, and real-world research and evidence enables clients to understand patients, physicians and payers, bring products to market quickly, navigate the regulatory pathway and negotiate payer reimbursement and coverage.
Kantar is providing insight and inspiration to help clients flourish in an extraordinary world, we bring together 12 of the world’s leading research, data and insight Divisions. Our global team of 30,000 people in more than 100 countries delivers specialist insight, business strategies and consultancy support.
KEY OUTCOMES
Runs, under the supervision of a Project Manager, the management of qualitative healthcare research studies, from set up to final report and presentation to end clients;
Excellent writing skills;
Good analysis and synthesis abilities;
Involved in the discussion of analysis axes with Project team and be in charge of the design of report template and the final report;
Interacts and coordinate international data collection suppliers to ascertain the quality and accuracy of the research;
Is involved in the discussion and in the management of clients;
Is involved, according to opportunities, in the oral presentation of study results to clients;
Commits to enhancing skills and knowledge, and seeks to expand level of responsibilities;
CAPABILITIES
Bac+5 or master’s degree; preferably in social science, sociology (Public Health) or psychology, biology studies, or HEOR/Public Health;
Minimum of a year of experience as a Research Analyst / Scientist / Healthcare Consultant;
Fluency in French and English (C2).
Involved in the production of qualitative research;
Follows up analysis and client servicing;
Any experience or significant interest towards the healthcare sector or pharma industry would be a plus.
Curious of the healthcare word and eager to acquire new skills.
Any experience of CAQDAS (computer-aided qualitative data analysis software) would be a plus
